### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Adds a feature as requested in #8044 

### What is the new behavior?
Progressive Web APP for Submitty.
Now the submitty can be installed much like an app on any platform(Mac,Android,ios,linux,etc). To install the application visit the user profile and click on the install app button present over there.

### Other information?
It does not break any feature or prevent you from doing anything that you were able to do earlier.This is in development phase , as there are a lot of feature that we wish to add to make the experince much more enhanced.

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Adds the feature as requested in #7437 
Student column moves with the grid during grading,which casuse difficulties in grading as TA/Instructor have to go back and forth between the student column and the column  to mark and  make sure that they are marking the same row.

### What is the new behavior?
Now the student and other info columns remain fixed in the place which makes the grading easier.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/92226302/178952623-f9db5b34-1762-43a3-8d4d-8cd8e1122a18.png)

### Other information?
<!-- Is this a breaking change? -->
<!-- How did you test -->

pr_body:
### What is the current behavior?
Fixes #7568  : Colors are hard coded  for numeric gradeables instead of using 'colors.css'. This mainly causes problems with the dark mode version of the site. 

### What is the new behavior?
Standard names for the colors are used as described in colors.css instead of hashcodes , also the color '#ff7777'(not available in colors.css) is replaced with '#ff9999'(available in colors.css).

The Numeric/Text gradeable table have an obnoxious white background when in dark mode.

### What is the current behavior?
Closes #7985 
In instructor UI for a course,
Go to`  "Grade Reports"> "Web-Based Rainbow Grades Generation" > "Messages"'`

In the  section, there should be a form text box allowing you to enter messages, but it is not displayed in the message is currently empty. 

### What is the new behavior?
Empty TextBox is displayed allowing you to add and save the message.
### Other information?
Here is the screenshot for same.

### What is the current behavior?
 Closes #7323:While being zoomed in on a PDF in the grading interface, when trying to scroll to the right,the tools available gets hidden and inaccessible.  

### What is the new behavior?
Zoomed in on a PDF in the grading interface, when trying to scroll to the right, the position of the toolbar doesn't change and hence the tools don't hide and are always available.
### Other information?
- [x] Tested locally

### What is the current behavior?
Fixes #6859, Earlier on create/edit gradeable page the side navigation panel contained scroll and if the content on the page increased in the size then the footer went hidden under the content.

### What is the new behavior?
The scroll from the side navigation is removed and is made consistent with general user interface of the application.

### Other information?
Here is the screenshot for same
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/92226302/171448817-f7bf5627-0fde-4b29-854f-e614487664d7.png)

[{'comment_id': 887418423, 'comment_body': 'Question: Is this min-height in this file needed ? The `global.css` will put the `#wrapper` CSS rule on every page with the `min-height: max-content;`. 

When I see it on firefox it seems the duplicate rules get ignored and the others are applied. Not sure if this is the same on other browsers. Would just removing the `min-height` in the electronic.css cause any issues instead?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 2, 1, 15, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'shailpatels', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 888263425, 'comment_body': "@Eceptonsu @shailpatels  I also though that global.css must do the work but ..
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/92226302/171699754-b3904d77-9549-456a-b0ae-ef7ccd22c7c0.png)
Here in the screenshot (firefox browser) , It derives the css component from electronic.css and without it , the property didn't worked.
Hence, addition there was done. 
On contrary, not adding the property to global.css still does the work(for this page) but I added to it to cover the corner cases that might have been left.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 2, 18, 24, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'immortalcodes', 'type': 'User'}]
